Numerical Integration with the Trapezoidal Rule
Project Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of the Trapezoidal Rule, a numerical integration method used to approximate the value of a definite integral. The method divides the integration interval into several equal subintervals and approximates the area under the curve using a series of trapezoids.
The calculation process involves evaluating the function at specified points, applying trapezoidal coefficients, summing the weighted function values, and computing the final integral approximation. This approach is particularly useful when analytical integration is difficult or unavailable.

